=09=09=09=09Arms race revisited?
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Fresh from meeting George Bush and being told that the United S=
tates would=20
build its national missile defence scheme whether Russia liked it or not,=
=20
President Vladimir Putin said that, if so, his country would increase its=
=20
nuclear power =01&many times over=018 by putting multiple warheads on its m=
issiles.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: Doing the normal thing E+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09A former foreign minister of France, Roland Dumas, found guilty=
 of corruption=20
in the Elf affair in President Fran?ois Mitterrand=01,s day, claimed two of=
=20
today=01,s ministers, including Hubert V,drine, the foreign minister, had k=
nown=20
full well what was going on.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09The patchy truce between Israel and the Palestinians continued,=
 though both=20
sides blamed the other for not sticking to the bargain. Colin Powell, Ameri=
ca=01,
s secretary of state, will be returning to the region. Israel reacted angri=
ly=20
to a BBC documentary about the possibility that Ariel Sharon, Israel=01,s p=
rime=20
minister, might be charged with war crimes for his indirect responsibility=
=20
for the massacre of Palestinian refugees in 1982.
