=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Collateral damage
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Iraq claimed that 23 people had been killed when American and B=
ritish=20
aircraft patrolling Iraq=01,s northern no-fly zone bombed land near Mosul t=
hat=20
was used as a football pitch. The Americans and the British deny the=20
incident.=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Police shot dead 13 people in India when a mob set fire to the =
state assembly=20
building in Imphal, the capital of Manipur. The rioters were protesting=20
against the Delhi government=01,s truce with Naga separatists in the state.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Frustrating the Algerian regime=01,s divide-and-rule tactics, p=
rotests that=20
started in the Berber-speaking region spread to other areas.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: The swelling anger of Algerians E+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09A bomb in an office of Bangladesh=01,s ruling Awami League kill=
ed 22 people. It=20
was the biggest of a series of blasts that have killed about 100 people in=
=20
the past two years. The opposition Bangladesh National Party denied=20
involvement in the attack.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Patients are a virtue
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09The United States Senate plunged into a dispute over a patients=
=01, bill of=20
rights. Arguing that it would raise health-care costs, Republicans delayed=
=20
action on the bill. The Democrats say they will keep the Senate in session=
=20
beyond its July 4th recess to pass it.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: Hillary, you won the war E+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09NATO said that, if there were a peace deal in Macedonia, it wou=
ld send up to=20
5,000 troops empowered, among other things, to collect weapons surrendered =
by=20
ethnic-Albanian guerrillas.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09An appeal court in California upheld a homeless man=01,s 25-yea=
r prison sentence=20
for stealing four biscuits. The man, jailed under California=01,s =01&three=
 strikes=20
and you=01,re out=018 policy, was said by the court to be a career criminal=
.
